value.title: Donald Trump, Assault Weapons, Prom: Your Weekend Briefing
value.excerpt: Donald Trump began his next act Saturday night at the North Carolina Republican convention. In a 90-minute speech, Mr. Trump ran through a litany of conservative culture war issues and ended with an extended frontal attack on voting and American democracy in which he endorsed a long list of Republican voter suppression proposals.

value.title: Trump endorses Ted Budd in North Carolina Senate GOP primary
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump on Saturday endorsed Rep. Ted Budd's campaign for Senate in North Carolina, making the surprise announcement just minutes after his daughter-in-law Lara Trump confirmed she would not be entering the Republican primary for the open seat in 2022.

value.title: Biden's Justice Department says it will no longer seize reporters' records for leak investigations
value.excerpt: The Justice Department on Saturday said it will no longer seize reporters' records in leak investigations, a notable policy shift on the heels of disclosures that federal prosecutors aggressively pursued communication data from reporters to identify their sources.

value.title: Analysis: You can believe in UFOs without believing Trump's election lies
value.excerpt: 2021 is shaping up to be the year of believing the unbelievable might be possible.

value.title: A favored Biden timeline for politically-charged decisions: Later
value.excerpt: The president seems to be reaching for a traditional executive branch stalling tactic at a higher rate than his predecessors.

value.title: Bipartisan lawmakers call on Biden to 'immediately' evacuate Afghans who helped the US
value.excerpt: A bipartisan group of lawmakers is calling on the Biden administration to immediately evacuate thousands of Afghans who have assisted the United States, saying in a letter Friday that those "Afghan friends and allies are at greater risk than ever before" as the US military withdrawal from the country

value.title: Biden administration plans to undo Trump-era curbs to Endangered Species Act protections
value.excerpt: The Biden administration announced on Friday plans to review and revise a handful of Trump-era regulations that critics feared rolled back protections for endangered and threatened species.

value.title: After 2-year battle, House panel to interview Trump counsel McGahn
value.excerpt: His interview with the Judiciary Committee comes two years after House Democrats originally sought his testimony as part of investigations into former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Mike Pence on Donald Trump: 'I don't know if we'll ever see eye to eye' on January 6
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence acknowledged on Thursday that he and former President Donald Trump maintain starkly different views of the riot that unfolded at the US Capitol on January 6.

value.title: In a speech to a New Hampshire G.O.P. group, Pence calls systemic racism a ‘left-wing myth.’
value.excerpt: Mike Pence also distanced himself from President Donald J. Trump, saying of the Capitol attack, “I don’t know if we’ll ever see eye-to-eye on that day.”

value.title: DOJ investigating Trump-appointed Postmaster General Louis DeJoy
value.excerpt: The Justice Department is investigating campaign contributions made by Postmaster General Louis DeJoy's private sector employees, his spokesman confirmed Thursday.

value.title: Queen Elizabeth announces she'll meet President Biden at Windsor Castle this month
value.excerpt: Britain's Queen Elizabeth will welcome US President Joe Biden to Windsor Castle on June 13, Buckingham Palace announced on Thursday.

value.title: Biden floats bringing down infrastructure price tag but wants GOP concessions
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden met with Republican Sen. Shelley Moore Capito of West Virginia at the White House on Wednesday as part of ongoing discussions between his administration and the Senate GOP on infrastructure.

value.title: 'Get a shot and have a beer': Biden's new glass-half-full strategy woos vaccine skeptics
value.excerpt: This Bud's for you, and anyone else ready to roll up their sleeve to put the pandemic behind them.

value.title: Robert Mueller to help teach law school class on Trump-Russia investigation
value.excerpt: Former special counsel Robert Mueller will help teach a University of Virginia Law School class on his investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 presidential election, the school announced Wednesday.

value.title: Biden will discuss recent cyber attack on meat producer with Putin in Geneva
value.excerpt: The White House says President Joe Biden will address the recent ransomware attack on a meat producer and the increased threat of cyber attacks while meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin later this month in Geneva.

value.title: Anheuser-Busch to give away free alcohol if US hits Biden's goal of 70% of adults with at least one Covid vaccine shot by July 4
value.excerpt: Anheuser-Busch, the national brewer that produces Budweiser, announced Wednesday it will give away free alcohol if the nation reaches President Joe Biden's goal to have 70% of US adults receive at least dose of the vaccine by July 4.

value.title: Harris aiming to deepen US relationship with Guatemala and Mexico on first foreign trip
value.excerpt: Kamala Harris will try to deepen the United States' "strategic partnership and bilateral relationship" with Guatemala and Mexico on her first foreign trip as vice president, according to her senior staff members.

value.title: Biden administration formally ends 'remain in Mexico' policy after suspending it earlier this year
value.excerpt: The Biden administration formally ended the Trump-era policy of returning asylum seekers to Mexico until their court dates in the United States, according to a memo issued by Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas.

value.title: Fact-checking Sidney Powell's claim Trump could be reinstated
value.excerpt: Months into President Joe Biden's first term, supporters of former President Donald Trump are still touting the "big lie" that Trump actually won the 2020 election. One of the prominent supporters of these theories is Trump's former lawyer Sidney Powell, who is facing a $1.3 billion defamation lawsuit

value.title: A tabloid publisher will pay a $187,500 F.E.C. penalty for its Trump hush-money payment.
value.excerpt: But Donald Trump faces no further investigation or penalties related to the 2016 payment to a former Playboy model by the publisher of The National Enquirer.

value.title: Biden proclaims day of remembrance on 100th anniversary of Tulsa Race Massacre
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Monday issued a proclamation to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the Tulsa Race Massacre, when hundreds of Black Americans were killed by a White mob that attacked a prosperous Black neighborhood and burned dozens of city blocks to the ground.

value.title: For Biden, the White House is 'a Monday-through-Friday kind of place'
value.excerpt: Beginning in 1973, when he was a United States Senator from Delaware, Joe Biden had a ritual: nearly every evening he would hop a train back to Wilmington after his work day on Capitol Hill, spending most nights and weekends at the place he considered home, 100 miles from Washington.

value.title: 'These attacks are despicable': Biden condemns rise in anti-Semitic incidents
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Friday condemned the rise in anti-Semitic attacks across the country in recent weeks, saying the incidents are "despicable, unconscionable, un-American, and they must stop."

value.title: Analysis: The one reason Biden's $6 trillion budget is so important
value.excerpt: Budgets in Washington seem about as meaningful as budgets for regular people.

value.title: Biden to sign order establishing White House initiative on Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians and Pacific Islanders
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden will sign an executive order on Friday renewing a White House initiative charged with advancing "equity, justice, and opportunity" for Asian Americans, Native Hawaiians and Pacific Islanders, including coordinating a "comprehensive" federal response to the rise in anti-Asian violence

value.title: Biden blasts Republicans for touting Covid relief funds they voted against: 'Some people have no shame'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Thursday criticized Republican lawmakers who have touted parts of the Covid-19 economic relief law that benefit their constituents despite having voted against the law, saying: "Some people have no shame."

value.title: Trump, Giuliani urge judge to throw out Democrats' Capitol riot lawsuit
value.excerpt: Giuliani's use of the phrase "trial by combat" during the rally that preceded the riot referred to future legal challenges, not anything happening at the Capitol, his lawyer said.

value.title: Republican governors face the Trump litmus test as elections approach
value.excerpt: Donald Trump is causing a headache for the Republican Governors Association.
